2. What was the founding story? What problem were you trying to solve?

Solidroad was founded by two ex-Intercom teammates and the mission is to improve the quality bar of every customer interaction. The company was co-founded by Mark Hughes (CEO) and Patrick Finlay (CTO). The pair met at Intercom where Mark worked in sales and Patrick was a product engineer. The problem they are looking to solve is how to manage quality across all your interactions when you have so many different channels, human agents, outsourced BPO vendors, and now AI deflection agent vendors taking customer conversations. 

3. What makes your approach different from existing solutions in the market?

Existing solutions were built with manual processes in mind. They were workflow tools for manual classroom-based training and manual QA audits. These solutions have bolted on AI, whereas Solidroad has built AI natively. Solidroad uses AI to review 100% of conversations in both simulated and live environments across every channel to give you a full understanding of your business and how you are interacting with your customers. Existing solutions only review a small portion of conversations. Those who claim they do full coverage don’t close the feedback loop by optimising and improving conversations going forward. 


